Package org.neo4j.internal.batchimport.staging

Class SpectrumExecutionMonitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.internal.batchimport.staging.ExecutionMonitor.Adapter
      • org.neo4j.internal.batchimport.staging.SpectrumExecutionMonitor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ExecutionMonitor
    public class SpectrumExecutionMonitor
extends ExecutionMonitor.Adapter
    This is supposed to be a beautiful one-line ExecutionMonitor, looking like: 
     NODE |--INPUT--|--NODE--|======NODE=PROPERTY======|-------------WRITER-------------| 1000
    where there's one line per stage, updated rapidly, overwriting the line each time. The width of the Step column is based on how slow it is compared to the others. The width of the "spectrum" is user specified, but is dynamic in that it can shrink or expand based on how many simultaneous executions this monitor is monitoring. The specified width is included stage identifier and progress, so in a console the whole console width can be specified.
